feat: add per-edge channel capacity override

Add `Pipe::with_capacity(n)` to override the default channel capacity
(1024) for the next downstream edge. The override is consumed by the
next edge-creating operation and not propagated to clones.

- Add `capacity_override: Option<usize>` field to `Pipe<T, D>`
- Add `resolve_capacity()` helper that takes override or falls back to
  builder config
- Update all edge-creating methods (map, filter, flat_map, unary,
  unary_notify, binary, iterate, concat, output, exchange,
  exchange_by_hash) to use resolved capacity
- Store per-edge capacity alongside exchange creators so spawn_multi and
  spawn_cluster use it instead of hardcoded 1024
- Iterate feedback/leave edges respect capacity overrides from the body
- Clone does not propagate capacity_override (prevents accidental reuse)
- Assert capacity > 0
- Add 7 tests covering basic usage, chaining, clone semantics, zero
  panic, small buffers, unary, and concat

Closes G1.2 from datafusion-gap-analysis.md

Co-authored-by: Copilot <223556219+Copilot@users.noreply.github.com>
